x4freetext: Spectra of high-energy photons following the capture
of 14 MeV neutrons by Cs-133, La-139, Ce and Tb-159
Time of flight is used to reduce the back-
12.7 cm diameter by 12.7 cm thick NaI(Tl)
The cross-sections are computed by integrating the
gamma spectrum over the excitation energy interval
from the kinetic energy of the neutrons to this
energy plus the neutron binding energy.
Comparisons of the measured cross sections with
the calculations based on the direct and collective
capture models are in good agreement.

Integrated cross section is close to other nuclei

4 to 10 with respect to those previously measured from
activation of nuclei with approximately the same mass.
